The paper discusses the use of active learning for identifying relevant studies in systematic reviews, which is a task commonly performed in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of different feature extraction models, which is a common topic in machine learning (ML) research, particularly in the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DL.
